Compute
\[\frac{(1 + 17) \left( 1 + \dfrac{17}{2} \right) \left( 1 + \dfrac{17}{3} \right) \dotsm \left( 1 + \dfrac{17}{19} \right)}{(1 + 19) \left( 1 + \dfrac{19}{2} \right) \left( 1 + \dfrac{19}{3} \right) \dotsm \left( 1 + \dfrac{19}{17} \right)}.\]
inference:
$$ \begin{split}\frac{(1 + 17) \left( 1 + \dfrac{17}{2} \right) \left( 1 + \dfrac{17}{3} \right) \dotsm \left( 1 + \dfrac{17}{19} \right)}{(1 + 19) \left( 1 + \dfrac{19}{2} \right) \left( 1 + \dfrac{19}{3} \right) \dotsm \left( 1 + \dfrac{19}{17} \right) } & = \frac{(17 + 1) (2 \cdot 17 + 1) (3 \cdot 17 + 1) \dotsm (19 \cdot 17 + 1)}{(19 + 1) (2 \cdot 19 + 1) (3 \cdot 19 + 1) \dotsm (17 \cdot 19 + 1) }  \\\ & = \frac{18 \cdot 35 \cdot 54 \dotsm 343}{20 \cdot 39 \cdot 58 \dotsm 323 }  \\\ & = \frac{ 2 \cdot 3^2 \cdot 6 \cdot 9 \dotsm 19^2 }{ 2^2 \cdot 5 \cdot 11 \cdot 17 \dotsm 19^2 }  \\\ & = \frac{3 \cdot 6}{5 \cdot 11}  \\\ & = \frac{18}{55}. \end{split} $$

Final Answer: \boxed{$ \frac{18}{55} $}. I hope it is correct.
